{"id":228884043,"title":"On smoothing and inference for topic models","authors":["Arthur Asuncion","Max Welling","Padhraic Smyth","Yee Whye Teh"],"_abstract":"Latent Dirichlet analysis, or topic modeling, is a flexible latent variable framework for model-ing high-dimensional sparse count data. Various learning algorithms have been developed in re-cent years, including collapsed Gibbs sampling, variational inference, and maximum a posteriori estimation, and this variety motivates the need for careful empirical comparisons. In this paper, we highlight the close connections between these approaches. We find that the main differences are attributable to the amount of smoothing applied to the counts. When the hyperparameters are op-timized, the differences in performance among the algorithms diminish significantly. The ability of these algorithms to achieve solutions of com-parable accuracy gives us the freedom to select computationally efficient approaches. Using the insights gained from this comparative study, we show how accurate topic models can be learned in several seconds on text corpora with thousands of documents.","cited_in":[{"id":285598004,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/285598004_Labor_market_demand_analysis_for_engineering_majors_in_Peru_using_Shallow_Parsing_and_Topic_Modeling"},{"id":283117540,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/283117540_A_'Gibbs-Newton'_Technique_for_Enhanced_Inference_of_Multivariate_Polya_Parameters_and_Topic_Models"},{"id":280292979,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/280292979_Making_the_Most_of_Crowdsourced_Document_Annotations_Confused_Supervised_LDA"},{"id":265843056,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/265843056_A_lead-lag_analysis_of_the_topic_evolution_patterns_for_preprints_and_publications_A_Lead-Lag_Analysis_of_the_Topic_Evaluation_Patterns_for_Preprints_and_Publications"},{"id":269722321,"url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/269722321_A_Scalable_Asynchronous_Dist